{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T03:53:28.574Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Kernels"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in machine learning are mathematical functions that compute "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "similarity between data points"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — they enable SVMs to handle non-linearly separable data by implicitly transforming the data into higher-dimensional space where linear separation becomes possible."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What They Are"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "kernel function"}, {"type": "text", "text": " "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "K(x_i, x_j)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " computes the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "dot product"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of two points in a higher-dimensional feature space "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "without explicitly transforming the data"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "K(x_i, x_j) = \\phi(x_i) \\cdot \\phi(x_j)"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\phi"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = transformation function to higher-dimensional space\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "K"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = kernel function (computes dot product in transformed space)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": The \"kernel trick\" lets SVM work with high-dimensional data "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "efficiently"}, {"type": "text", "text": " without actually computing the transformation."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Kernels Matter"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Problem"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Solution with Kernels"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Non-linearly separable data"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transform to higher dimension where linear separation works"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Explicit transformation expensive"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compute dot product directly in transformed space"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Complex decision boundaries"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learn non-linear boundaries via kernel mapping"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High-dimensional feature space"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Works efficiently in implicit high dimensions"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Real-world necessity"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": In real-world data, classes often aren't linearly separable in the original feature space."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Kernels Work: The Kernel Trick"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 4}, "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step 1: Original Space (2D)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Data: Points that cannot be separated by a straight line\n      ● ×\n      × ●\n      ● ×\n      × ●"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cannot separate with linear hyperplane."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 4}, "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step 2: Transform to Higher Dimension"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Map: (x₁, x₂) → (x₁, x₂, x₁² + x₂²) [3D]\n     \nNow: Points separated by a plane\n      ________\n     /|      /|\n    / |     / |\n   ●  |    ×  |\n   |  |    |  |\n   |  ×    |  ●\n   | /     | /\n   |/      |/"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 4}, "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step 3: Use Kernel to Compute Dot Product"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Instead of computing "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\phi(x_i)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " explicitly:\n$$K(x_i, x_j) = \\phi(x_i) \\cdot \\phi(x_j)$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Kernel computes the result "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "directly"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Kernel Types"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Kernels — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Linear Kernel"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$K(x_i, x_j) = x_i \\cdot x_j$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it does"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": No transformation — uses original features directly"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Not Ideal When"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Linearly separable data"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Non-linear patterns"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "High-dimensional data"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (e.g., text)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Complex decision boundaries"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large datasets"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (faster training)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Need for non-linear boundaries"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Text classification with many features."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Polynomial Kernel"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$K(x_i, x_j) = (x_i \\cdot x_j + c)^d$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "d"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = degree of polynomial\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "c"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = constant (controls influence of higher vs lower degree terms)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it does"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Maps data to polynomial feature space of degree "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "d"}}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Not Ideal When"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Curved boundaries needed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large degree (computationally expensive)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Medium complexity patterns"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Need smooth boundaries"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature interactions important"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Very high-dimensional data"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Mapping 2D features "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "(x_1, x_2)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " to 3D: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "(x_1, x_2, x_1^{2}, x_2^{2}, x_1x_2)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "RBF Kernel"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Radial Basis Function / Gaussian)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Most popular"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for non-linear SVM problems."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$K(x_i, x_j) = \\exp(-\\gamma \\|x_i - x_j\\|^2)$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\gamma"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " (gamma) = hyperparameter controlling influence of single training example\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\|x_i - x_j\\|^2"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = squared Euclidean distance between points"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it does"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Maps data to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "infinite-dimensional"}, {"type": "text", "text": " space"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Properties"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Creates "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "smooth, non-linear"}, {"type": "text", "text": " decision boundaries\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Universal kernel"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Works for most non-linear problems\n- Most commonly used kernel in practice"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Not Ideal When"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Non-linear patterns"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (most common)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Linearly separable data (use linear)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "No prior knowledge"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of data structure"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Very large datasets (slow training)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Complex decision boundaries"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Need interpretable model"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Handwriting recognition, image classification."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sigmoid Kernel"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$K(x_i, x_j) = \\tanh(\\alpha x_i \\cdot x_j + c)$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\alpha"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = scaling parameter\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "c"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = constant"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "What it does"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Logistic-like transformation"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Not Ideal When"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Multi-class problems"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Binary classification (RBF better)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Neural network-like behavior"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Simple linear patterns"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "5. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gaussian RBF Kernel"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Soft K-NN)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$K(x^{(i)}, x) = \\exp\\left(-\\gamma \\|x^{(i)} - x\\|^2\\right)$$"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\gamma \\geq 0"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = hyperparameter controlling smoothness of "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "f"}}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Special property"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": SVC (Support Vector Classification) works like "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "K-NN"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in some sense\n- Each training example contributes to decision function\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sparse kernel machine"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Only support vectors (with "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "a_i > 0"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ") matter"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Kernel in SVM Decision Function"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The SVM classifier uses kernel in its prediction formula:"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "f(x) = \\sum_{i=1}^{N} a_i y_i K(x_i, x) + b"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "a_i"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Lagrange multipliers (only non-zero for support vectors)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "y_i"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = class label (+1 or -1)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "K(x_i, x)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = kernel function (similarity between training point "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x_i"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " and new point "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ")\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "b"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = bias"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Only "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "support vectors"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (with "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "a_i > 0"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ") contribute to decision function → sparse representation."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Kernel Matrix (Gram Matrix)"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "For $n$ training points, the **kernel matrix** $K$ is an $n \\times n$ matrix: [medium](https://medium.com/@dswithgk/support-vector-machines-svm-the-kernel-trick-a-comprehensive-guide-part-i-6a6b16d346ca)"}}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "K_{ij} = K(x_i, x_j)"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Uses"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Solves the dual SVM optimization problem\n- Each element represents similarity between pair of points\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Time complexity"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "O(D)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " to evaluate "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "K_{ij}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "O(ND)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " for classification"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparison Table: Kernels"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Kernel"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Transformation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best For"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Complexity"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Linear"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "None (original space)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Linearly separable, high-dimensional"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": nu